I"]<h3 id="about-me">About me</h3>

<p>I am currently a Byrne Instructor in Applied Mathematics. My mentor is <a href="https://math.dartmouth.edu/~annegelb/">Prof. Anne Gelb</a>. <strong>I am on the job market this year.</strong></p>

<p>I received my Ph.D in Applied Mathematics in 2020 from the Department of Mathematics, UC Davis, advised by <a href="http://math.ucdavis.edu/~qlxia">Prof. Qinglan Xia</a>. My dissertation topic is <strong>From optimal transport to optimal mixing flows and vice versa</strong>.</p>

<p>Prior to that, I received my B.S in Mathematics and Applied Mathematics in 2014 from Zhejiang University and finished my undergraduate thesis supervised by <a href="http://www.math.zju.edu.cn/linzhi/">Prof. Zhi (George) Lin</a>.</p>

